        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "These are some valid IPs which are said to be incorrect by Zend_Validate_Ip:\r\n2001:0db8:0000:0000:0000:0000:1428:57ab\r\n2001:0DB8:0000:0000:0000:0000:1428:57AB\r\na:b:c::1.2.3.4\r\na:b:c:d::1.2.3.4\r\na:b:c:d:e::1.2.3.4\r\na:b:c:d:e:f:1.2.3.4\r\na::c:d:e:f:0:1\r\na::0:1\r\n::e:f\r\na:b:c:d:e:f::0\r\n\r\nFound here ( http:\/\/therealcrisp.xs4all.nl\/blog\/article-content\/ipv6\/ipv6.phps ) via (  http:\/\/crisp.tweakblogs.net\/blog\/3049\/ipv6-validation-more-caveats.html and http:\/\/crisp.tweakblogs.net\/blog\/2031\/ipv6-validation-(and-caveats).html )"
